The fix is complete. Here's what was done:

**Root cause (two-layer bug):**
1. `Generate.tsx` line 94: `historyDefaults ?? lsDefaults ?? (topicFromUrl ? ...)` — `lsDefaults` is non-nullish (has `topic: ""`), so `topicFromUrl` was never reached
2. `ToolForm.tsx` line 70: `{...resolvedDefaults, ...parsed}` — LS spread would override `topic` even if `resolvedDefaults.topic` was non-empty

**Fixes:**
1. `Generate.tsx`: Changed to `historyDefaults ?? (topicFromUrl ? {...lsDefaults, topic: topicFromUrl} : lsDefaults)` — preserves other LS fields (scriptType, elements) but `topicFromUrl` wins on `topic`
2. `ToolForm.tsx`: Changed to `{...resolvedDefaults, ...parsed, ...(resolvedDefaults.topic ? {topic: resolvedDefaults.topic} : {})}` — protects non-empty `resolvedDefaults.topic` from LS override

All 2250 tests pass, typecheck clean.
